CIA Triad Research

1. Confidentiality
Definition
Confidentiality refers to protecting sensitive information from unauthorized access and disclosure.
Only authorized users should be able to view or access the data.

Why It Is Important
Confidentiality helps protect personal information, financial records, business data, and other sensitive information from cybercriminals and unauthorized users.

Real-World Example
Online banking systems use usernames, passwords, and encryption to ensure that only account holders can access their financial information.

2. Integrity
Definition
Integrity ensures that data remains accurate, complete, and unchanged unless modified by an authorized person.

Why It Is Important
Organizations rely on accurate information for decision-making. Unauthorized changes to data can result in incorrect records, financial losses, and loss of trust.

Real-World Example
A college examination system must ensure that student grades cannot be altered by unauthorized individuals.


3. Availability
Definition
Availability ensures that systems, applications, and data are accessible whenever authorized users need them.

Why It Is Important
If important systems become unavailable, business operations, education services, and communication can be disrupted.

Real-World Example
A college website should remain accessible during admissions, examinations, and result announcements.



Comparison Table

| CIA Component   | Definition                                                   | Importance                                    | Real-World Example    |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------- | --------------------- |
| Confidentiality | Protects data from unauthorized access                       | Maintains privacy and security of information | Online Banking System |
| Integrity       | Ensures data accuracy and prevents unauthorized modification | Maintains trust in information                | Examination Records   |
| Availability    | Ensures systems and data are accessible when needed          | Supports continuous operations                | College Website       |

# Conclusion

The CIA Triad forms the foundation of cybersecurity. Confidentiality protects information from unauthorized access, 
Integrity ensures data remains accurate and trustworthy, and Availability guarantees that systems and services remain accessible.
Together, these three principles help organizations secure their information and maintain reliable operations.
